## Example 2 — Describe Center and Spread Using a Histogram

Describe the center and spread of a data set using either the mean and standard deviation or the five-number summary. Justify the choice by constructing a histogram.

### Step 1: Construct a Histogram

Create a histogram to visualize the shape of the distribution.

### Step 2: Determine the Shape

Examine the histogram to decide whether the distribution is symmetric or skewed. Look for tails, gaps, or clusters.

### Step 3: Choose and Calculate Statistics

* If symmetric, report the mean [ \bar{x} ] and standard deviation [ \sigma ] 
* If skewed or containing outliers, report the five-number summary: [ \text{min}, Q_1, \text{median}, Q_3, \text{max} ] 

